articles.title: Morocco dinosaur discovery gives clues on why they went extinct - Phys.org
articles.description: 66 million years ago, the last dinosaurs vanished from Earth. We're still trying to understand why. New fossils of abelisaurs—distant relatives of the tyrannosaurs—from north Africa suggest that African dinosaurs remained diverse up to the very end. And that …
